1
00:00:00,127 --> 00:00:01,960
Interviewer: When they brought you into the hall

2
00:00:02,342 --> 00:00:05,106
And the time for the afternoon prayer came, and it was your first prayer here

3
00:00:06,853 --> 00:00:10,805
Were you in <i>wudu</i> [ritual purity], or did you tell them you wanted to do your ablutions?

4
00:00:10,898 --> 00:00:12,255
Or did they force you to wash?

5
00:00:12,482 --> 00:00:14,815
No, he said, Who among you is not in <i>wudu</i>?

6
00:00:15,083 --> 00:00:17,315
I told him I was, and we went out—we were four or five people

7
00:00:18,321 --> 00:00:19,349
Those who were before us

8
00:00:20,115 --> 00:00:22,085
Had already performed <i>wudu</i> and prayed the noon prayer

9
00:00:22,672 --> 00:00:23,672
Then we came

10
00:00:24,694 --> 00:00:26,475
We performed <i>wudu</i> and returned to the hall to pray

11
00:00:27,195 --> 00:00:29,340
Here, here

12
00:00:29,992 --> 00:00:32,109
These faucets were here

13
00:00:32,956 --> 00:00:34,466
We performed <i>wudu</i> and went out

14
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:35,494
Did you perform <i>wudu</i> and relieve yourself?

15
00:00:35,521 --> 00:00:36,527
No, I only performed <i>wudu</i>

16
00:00:36,898 --> 00:00:38,460
Interviewer: Only in this place? Witness: Yes

17
00:00:38,534 --> 00:00:42,515
Interviewer: From when you came from the hall until you performed <i>wudu</i> and returned?

18
00:00:42,843 --> 00:00:44,483
Were guards escorting you, or were you alone?

19
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,714
One of them was standing here

20
00:00:47,868 --> 00:00:49,006
And another was standing there

21
00:00:49,753 --> 00:00:51,277
And another was standing in the corridor

22
00:00:52,257 --> 00:00:53,836
As you know, you cannot

23
00:00:54,398 --> 00:00:59,016
I looked to the right and left, searching for
A place to escape—I looked, but there was none

24
00:00:59,439 --> 00:01:02,036
Interviewer: Did he come to you?
Witness: Yes, of course

25
00:01:02,452 --> 00:01:06,655
And here you do not know your fate, whether they will flog you or imprison you

26
00:01:07,416 --> 00:01:10,501
If they imprison you for fifteen days

27
00:01:10,795 --> 00:01:12,040
And your family knows nothing about you

28
00:01:12,594 --> 00:01:14,706
And God forbid, a plane might bomb you and you would die

29
00:01:16,019 --> 00:01:17,106
No one knows anything about you

30
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:20,522
I looked to the right and left, and I am from this area

31
00:01:21,415 --> 00:01:25,149
I looked for a way, and through the roof I thought I could reach it

32
00:01:25,821 --> 00:01:27,944
I saw the place was crowded, and the idea of escape was hard

33
00:01:28,551 --> 00:01:33,221
Interviewer: The prefab houses and rooms around us, and the destroyed places?

34
00:01:33,754 --> 00:01:36,062
Do you remember what they were used for?

35
00:01:36,435 --> 00:01:38,248
Or did you not see them or pay attention to them?

36
00:01:38,375 --> 00:01:39,771
I did not pay attention to them in those days

37
00:01:40,119 --> 00:01:42,787
As I told you, they used these rooms for the prison

38
00:01:43,507 --> 00:01:46,381
It was for temporary detention, like two or three days

39
00:01:47,201 --> 00:01:48,201
Or five days

40
00:01:48,792 --> 00:01:50,312
And after that they would transfer them

41
00:01:50,475 --> 00:01:52,674
Interviewer: Were the rooms partitioned?
Witness: Yes, they were partitioned

42
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,774
Interviewer: When you went out for <i>wudu</i>?

43
00:01:55,170 --> 00:01:58,012
The first <i>wudu</i>, at the very start of your time in the place

44
00:01:58,272 --> 00:01:59,272
And it was new to you

45
00:01:59,487 --> 00:02:01,974
While you went for <i>wudu</i> and came back?

46
00:02:02,261 --> 00:02:06,305
Didn't you hear torture, the voices of prisoners present? Screams?

47
00:02:06,871 --> 00:02:08,573
Women's voices? Didn't you hear anything like that?

48
00:02:08,627 --> 00:02:09,629
No, I did not hear them

49
00:02:09,945 --> 00:02:11,376
Interviewer: You did not hear?
Witness: No

50
00:02:11,587 --> 00:02:15,382
As I told you, torture does not happen here, and harsh torture does not happen here

51
00:02:16,335 --> 00:02:18,967
Like <i>falaqa</i> [foot whipping] and other methods of torture

52
00:02:20,456 --> 00:02:22,400
Nothing happens here because it is only temporary

53
00:02:22,926 --> 00:02:23,980
He is presented to the sharia

54
00:02:25,059 --> 00:02:26,099
And whoever did not confess

55
00:02:28,336 --> 00:02:29,512
This is what God has decreed for him

56
00:02:29,618 --> 00:02:31,080
Interviewer: By sharia, do you mean the judge?

57
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:32,412
Witness: Yes, their sharia judge
